messages.message:
I did the fix as suggested on the crafting thread, I made some progress now it is stuck at 40% while uploading
everything in api-server seems fine though, Job service also looks good, I will work on something else in the meanwhile until we can precisely nail it down.
@Serena When you are back, Could you suggest what else I need to look for?
you need to look at the logs in celery-app-tasks to figure out why the digitization job is stuck

in `celery-app-task` logs, i see `DEADLINE_EXCEEDED` errors from model-service (ss1)

in `job-service` logs, i see `Unexpected error getting job state for failed task [TaskID=3e2ca2ff-ca2a-4e00-a409-5fb5a919a2dc-build-process-files, Reason='Failed to store project_docs : Project Docs cannot be empty or None']` (ss2)

`model-service` is not running properly in your environment - see the build issue in ss1

the fix for this was already mentioned last week (https://instabase.slack.com/archives/C05L87V014J/p1753388110844289)

@anik.b in the future, can you double check that all services are running properly and check <#C05L87V014J|> for any relevant fixes for those services?

for now, i've added `"601729033846.dkr.ecr.us-east-2.amazonaws.com (http://601729033846.dkr.ecr.us-east-2.amazonaws.com)": "ecr-login"` to `~/.docker/config.json`, and `model-service` seems to be building successfully

`model-service` successfully built but crashed bc of your change in `shared-utils/py-utils/utils/src/py/instabase/config_utils/feature_flags.py`

you need to make sure to follow `make build-protos` so that your changes are propagated to auto-generated proto files

since you haven't done that yet, `model-service` is crashing, which is causing digitization to fail
I just generated those proto files, model-service looks fine, nonetheless it doesn't work.
`model-service` was not running properly on your crafting environment - see screenshot of `cs logs -f model-service`
i assume you did `cs restart`? it seems `model-service` is running successfully now!
